title: Explosive Remnants of War Clearance in Georgia
description: Australia's funding will contribute to a Partnership for Peace Trust Fund project managed by the North Atlantic Treaty Organisation (NATO) for explosive remnats of war clearance and medical rehabilitation support to Georgia. The project seeks to develop and enhance Georgia's Explosive Ordnance Disposal (EOD) capacity through the acquisition of specialist EOD equipment and training. The project will establish a medical rehabilitation centre by procuring physical rehabilitation equipment and associated training for medical personnel.
